  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Defendant Kendra C Putman in court with attorney David L Herring.  Melissa J. Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1 and 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.
  The Defendant was sentenced as follows:

Count #1:

JAIL: 3 Days, apply 3 days credit, time served. (concurrent to count #2)

COSTS: $253.00 (to be paid at $25.00 per month commencing 2/1/18 or serve 18 days jail, consecutive, as penalty for non payment of fine);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00, to be paid at $25.00 per month consecutive to payment of fine.  Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

COMMUNITY SERVICE:  The Defendant is to perform 25 Hours within 1 year, to be monitored by WCS. Defendant to serve 20 days Jail, consecutive, as penalty for failure to complete community service.
Court authorizes credit towards costs/fine to be at the rate of $10.00/hour. Adjustment will be made upon proof of completion. 

Count #2:

JAIL: 3 Days, apply 3 days credit, time served. (concurrent to count #1)

COSTS: $243.00 (to be paid as part of payment plan on count #1);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00, to be paid as part of payment plan on Count #1. Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
